---
import BaseLayout from '../../components/layout/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '../../components/layout/Breadcrumb.astro';
import AlertBox from '../../components/wiki/AlertBox.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="GTA 6 Gameplay - Features & Mechanics | GTA6 Wikis"
  description="Complete GTA 6 gameplay breakdown — driving, shooting, stealth, dual protagonist system, wanted level, mini-games, and GTA Online 2 preview."
  canonicalUrl="https://gta6wikis.com/gta-6/gameplay/"
>
  <div class="page-wrapper">
    <div class="container">
      <Breadcrumb items={[
        { label: 'GTA 6', href: '/gta-6/' },
        { label: 'Gameplay' }
      ]} />
    </div>

    <header class="page-header">
      <div class="container">
        <h1 class="page-header__title">GTA 6 Gameplay</h1>
        <p class="page-header__desc">Features and mechanics confirmed from trailers, leaks, and official sources.</p>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="container main-content">

      <!-- Nav -->
      <nav class="section-nav" aria-label="Gameplay sections">
        <a href="#driving">Driving</a>
        <a href="#combat">Combat</a>
        <a href="#stealth">Stealth</a>
        <a href="#dual-protagonist">Dual Protagonists</a>
        <a href="#wanted">Wanted System</a>
        <a href="#activities">Activities</a>
        <a href="#online">GTA Online 2</a>
      </nav>

      <!-- Driving -->
      <section id="driving" class="section" aria-labelledby="driving-heading">
        <h2 class="section__title" id="driving-heading">Driving System</h2>
        <p>The driving engine in GTA 6 has been substantially reworked. Weather conditions directly affect vehicle handling — rain, mud, heat, and flooded streets change tire grip in real time. The feel is closer to a simulation-leaning arcade experience, with comparisons drawn to Forza Horizon and The Crew.</p>
        <div class="feature-grid">
          <div class="feature-card">
            <h3 class="feature-card__title">Weather-Affected Handling</h3>
            <p>Rain and flooded roads reduce grip. Mud affects acceleration and turning. Heat creates shimmer effects and surface-level changes to traction.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature-card">
            <h3 class="feature-card__title">Tire Physics</h3>
            <p>Tires respond differently to wet tarmac, mud, and off-road terrain. Different surface types require adjusted driving techniques.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature-card">
            <h3 class="feature-card__title">Customization Affects Feel</h3>
            <p>Installing larger wheels increases ride bumpiness and reduces smoothness. Mechanical modifications have direct gameplay consequences.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature-card">
            <h3 class="feature-card__title">First-Person Cockpit</h3>
            <p>All vehicles have fully modeled interiors. First-person and third-person driving modes are both supported.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <AlertBox type="info" title="200+ Vehicles">
          Over 200 vehicles have already been confirmed, with estimates suggesting 300+ at launch across land, air, and water. Types include sports cars, pick-up trucks, motorcycles, helicopters, seaplanes, jet skis, yachts, and monster trucks.
        </AlertBox>
      </section>

      <!-- Combat -->
      <section id="combat" class="section" aria-labelledby="combat-heading">
        <h2 class="section__title" id="combat-heading">Shooting &amp; Combat</h2>
        <p>Combat systems have been redesigned across shooting, vehicle combat, and melee.</p>

        <h3 class="subsection-h3">Shooting</h3>
        <ul class="detail-list">
          <li>Revised weapon wheel allows switching between weapons, gear, and equipment using R1/RB for quick swap</li>
          <li>Limited weapon storage replaces GTA V's unlimited supply — players must manage what they carry</li>
          <li>Shooting from car windows, truck beds, and even while swimming is supported</li>
          <li>More tactical options based on weapon choice, environment, and enemy movement patterns</li>
          <li>Realistic weapon animations and overhauled sound design</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="subsection-h3">Melee Combat</h3>
        <p>The melee system has been significantly expanded. Lucia's cage fighting scenes in the trailers demonstrate a dedicated hand-to-hand combat engine. Players can increase strength, agility, and endurance stats that directly affect melee effectiveness.</p>
        <ul class="detail-list">
          <li>Jason can throw NPCs through car windows</li>
          <li>Environmental objects — lampposts, benches, parked vehicles — can be used as weapons</li>
          <li>Physics-driven attacks create cinematic interactions with destructible objects</li>
          <li>Players who use their environment gain tactical advantages in fights</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- Stealth -->
      <section id="stealth" class="section" aria-labelledby="stealth-heading">
        <h2 class="section__title" id="stealth-heading">Stealth System</h2>
        <p>GTA 6 features a refined stealth and cover system, expanding on the mechanics introduced in GTA V.</p>
        <div class="feature-grid">
          <div class="feature-card">
            <h3 class="feature-card__title">Crouch Mechanic</h3>
            <p>Confirmed. Prone (lying flat) has been removed from the final build.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature-card">
            <h3 class="feature-card__title">Detection System</h3>
            <p>Enemy detection factors in lighting, shadows, noise level, and environmental interaction — not just line-of-sight.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature-card">
            <h3 class="feature-card__title">Mission Flexibility</h3>
            <p>Missions can be approached with direct force, full stealth, or any combination. AI and mission design adapt to player choices.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature-card">
            <h3 class="feature-card__title">Tools &amp; Gadgets</h3>
            <p>Various tools help players evade detection and complete missions undetected.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Dual Protagonist -->
      <section id="dual-protagonist" class="section" aria-labelledby="dual-heading">
        <h2 class="section__title" id="dual-heading">Dual Protagonist System</h2>
        <p>For the first time in the GTA series, the game launches with exactly two playable protagonists: Lucia Caminos and Jason Duval.</p>

        <div class="protagonist-grid">
          <div class="protagonist-card">
            <h3 class="protagonist-card__name">Lucia Caminos</h3>
            <p class="protagonist-card__role">Skills: Hacking, agility, cage fighting</p>
            <ul class="protagonist-card__list">
              <li>First female protagonist in mainline GTA</li>
              <li>Father taught her combat from childhood</li>
              <li>Hacking ability as a special skill</li>
              <li>Confirmed cage fighting combat sequences</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="protagonist-card">
            <h3 class="protagonist-card__name">Jason Duval</h3>
            <p class="protagonist-card__role">Skills: Dead-eye style aim, physical strength</p>
            <ul class="protagonist-card__list">
              <li>Former military — infantry background</li>
              <li>Precision aiming skill (similar to RDR2 Dead Eye)</li>
              <li>Higher raw physical strength</li>
              <li>Can throw enemies through car windows</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h3 class="subsection-h3">Character Switching</h3>
        <ul class="detail-list">
          <li>Players can seamlessly switch between Jason and Lucia during gameplay</li>
          <li>Each character has a separate skill tree and unique abilities</li>
          <li>Certain missions are designed for cooperative play between both characters</li>
          <li>Different characters offer different perspectives on story events</li>
        </ul>
        <AlertBox type="tip" title="Different from GTA V">
          Unlike GTA V's three-character system, GTA 6 focuses entirely on two protagonists with deeper individual development. The story is built around their partnership rather than parallel separate arcs.
        </AlertBox>
      </section>

      <!-- Wanted System -->
      <section id="wanted" class="section" aria-labelledby="wanted-heading">
        <h2 class="section__title" id="wanted-heading">Wanted System</h2>
        <p>The wanted level system in GTA 6 has been reworked to be more dynamic and context-sensitive.</p>
        <ul class="detail-list">
          <li>Wanted levels adapt based on the player's appearance and vehicle — changing clothes or swapping cars can help lose a pursuit</li>
          <li>Police AI responds more intelligently to evidence, witness reports, and environmental cues</li>
          <li>NPCs react more dynamically — bystanders may call police, flee, or intervene</li>
          <li>Enhanced AI for officer behavior during pursuits</li>
          <li>Dynamic random events include police chases and large-scale public disturbances</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- Activities -->
      <section id="activities" class="section" aria-labelledby="activities-heading">
        <h2 class="section__title" id="activities-heading">Activities &amp; Side Content</h2>
        <p>GTA 6 is expected to have a significant volume of side content and optional activities beyond the main story.</p>
        <div class="feature-grid">
          <div class="feature-card">
            <h3 class="feature-card__title">Cage Fighting</h3>
            <p>Confirmed activity for Lucia. A dedicated combat sport mode with upgradeable stats.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature-card">
            <h3 class="feature-card__title">Heists &amp; Robberies</h3>
            <p>Multiple robbery missions confirmed from trailers including bank heists and armed stick-ups. More types expected throughout.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature-card">
            <h3 class="feature-card__title">Social Media Integration</h3>
            <p>In-world "Finger" platform (a TikTok/Instagram analog) features NPCs recording content. Players can interact with the in-game social media ecosystem.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature-card">
            <h3 class="feature-card__title">Dynamic Random Events</h3>
            <p>Random events occur naturally as players explore — police chases, accidents, criminal activity, and public disturbances.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature-card">
            <h3 class="feature-card__title">100+ Main Missions</h3>
            <p>Over 100 main story missions expected. Each mission supports multiple completion approaches.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature-card">
            <h3 class="feature-card__title">Enterable Buildings</h3>
            <p>Approximately 70% of buildings have detailed interiors and can be entered, compared to roughly 30% in GTA V.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- GTA Online 2 -->
      <section id="online" class="section" aria-labelledby="online-heading">
        <h2 class="section__title" id="online-heading">GTA Online 2</h2>
        <p>GTA 6 ships with a new multiplayer experience officially called GTA Online 2 (or GTA Online Generation 2). It is a completely separate experience from GTA 5's GTA Online.</p>
        <AlertBox type="warning" title="Progress Does Not Transfer">
          GTA 5 Online progress, money, and properties cannot be transferred to GTA Online 2. It is a fresh start for all players.
        </AlertBox>
        <ul class="detail-list">
          <li>Launches alongside the main game (not as a separate release)</li>
          <li>Built on the same Leonida map as the story mode</li>
          <li>New online economy and progression systems</li>
          <li>Multiplayer DLC expected post-launch (consistent with Rockstar's GTA V support model)</li>
          <li>Single-player DLC is unlikely based on Rockstar's post-GTA V approach</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-wrapper {
    min-height: 100vh;
  }

  .container {
    max-width: 960px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 1.5rem;
  }

  /* Page Header */
  .page-header {
    background: linear-gradient(160deg, var(--bg-secondary) 0%, var(--bg-primary) 100%);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    padding: 2.5rem 0;
  }

  .page-header__title {
    font-family: 'Bebas Neue', sans-serif;
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 7vw, 4.5rem);
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  }

  .page-header__desc {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* Section nav */
  .section-nav {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    margin: 2rem 0;
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    border-radius: 10px;
  }

  .section-nav a {
    font-size: 0.825rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    text-decoration: none;
    padding: 0.3rem 0.75rem;
    border-radius: 6px;
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    transition: all 0.15s ease;
  }

  .section-nav a:hover {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    border-color: var(--color-accent);
    background: rgba(255, 94, 77, 0.06);
  }

  /* Main */
  .main-content {
    padding-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  /* Sections */
  .section {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    padding-bottom: 2.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
  }

  .section:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .section__title {
    font-family: 'Bebas Neue', sans-serif;
    font-size: 2rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }

  .section p {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .subsection-h3 {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin: 1.5rem 0 0.75rem;
  }

  /* Feature grid */
  .feature-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(220px, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
    margin: 1.25rem 0;
  }

  .feature-card {
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 1.1rem 1.25rem;
  }

  .feature-card__title {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }

  .feature-card p {
    font-size: 0.825rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.55;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* Detail list */
  .detail-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }

  .detail-list li {
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  .detail-list li::before {
    content: '→';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    top: 0.05em;
  }

  /* Protagonist grid */
  .protagonist-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.25rem;
    margin: 1.25rem 0;
  }

  .protagonist-card {
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
  }

  .protagonist-card__name {
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin: 0 0 0.3rem;
  }

  .protagonist-card__role {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 0.875rem;
  }

  .protagonist-card__list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.4rem;
  }

  .protagonist-card__list li {
    font-size: 0.825rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    padding-left: 1rem;
    position: relative;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .protagonist-card__list li::before {
    content: '•';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .feature-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .section-nav {
      gap: 0.4rem;
    }
  }
</style>
